Backport a configurable OpenRouter Fusion panel to opencode.

opencode 1.16.2 cannot configure a custom Fusion panel: the openrouter/fusion
model only ever runs OpenRouter's default Quality preset, with no way to pick
the analysis models or judge (anomalyco/opencode#32219). This backports the
variants() mechanism from PR anomalyco/opencode#32332, generalized so the preset
table is not hard-coded: openRouterFusionVariants() ships builtin quality/budget
panels and merges any presets injected via the OPENCODE_FUSION_PRESETS env var
(JSON: name -> { analysis_models, model }), so each profile supplies its own
panel + judge without editing this patch.

Targets opencode 1.16.2 (anomalyco/opencode).

